Spec. for ASUS PD3.0 65W 62368 ADATPER confidential

This specification define the input, output, performance characteristics, environment,
noise and safety requirements for the power supply.

-Normal voltage: 100~240Vrms
-Voltage Range: 90~264Vrms

-Normal Frequency: 50~60Hz
-Frequency Range: 47~63Hz
-Under 1.5A Irms at 100Vac & Max. load

-2 Conductors (Line, Neutral)
Spec. for ASUS PD3.0 65W 62368 ADATPER confidential
-An adequate internal fuse on the AC input line shall be provided.

-The inrush current of the power supply shall be less than the rating of its critical
components (include bridge diode, surge limiting device) for all condition of line
voltage of 2.1.1
-The I^2t shall less than 22% of the fuse, surge limiting device and bridge diode
rating.

-The power supply shall meet DOE VI / COC V5 Tier 2 spec measuring at the cable end.

Spec. for ASUS PD3.0 65W 62368 ADATPER confidential

-The total output voltage regulation shall be meet the spec., including the effects of
AC line voltage variation, load current, ripple and noise.
-The effect of transient load changes is included in this limit.
- Must comply with “Universal Serial Bus Power Delivery Specification Rev. 3.0”.

-The output overshoot at turn on shall not exceed 10% of normal voltage value with or
without the load connected.

-The power supply shall maintain voltage regulation within the specified limits in
paragraph 2.2.1 for at least 5ms after lost of input voltage measured at 100Vac and
maximum output load.

-At turn on the rise time of output voltage shall be less than 40ms.
＊Measured from the 10% point to the 90% point of the normal.
Spec. for ASUS PD3.0 65W 62368 ADATPER confidential

-No Load Power Consumption supply shall reach voltage regulation within the
specified limits in table 2.2.1 for 3sec max. after AC input the power supply.
-The input voltage measure at 100/240Vac and at maximum output load.

-Maximum no load power consumption is less than 0.075W at 115Vac/60Hz and
230Vac/50Hz

The adapter shall support a surge load with 120% of maximum load for 1min, maximum
load for 9min and output voltage shall be more than 18.5V/13.7V at 100-240Vac/50Hz-60Hz.

The adapter shall support below loading condition without any damage, safety issues
and protection happened. The output voltage shall be more than 17.8V (20V Mode) /
13.0V (15V Mode) at input voltage 100-240V/50Hz-60Hz.

Spec. for ASUS PD3.0 65W 62368 ADATPER confidential

-Plugging a live AC adapter into the system with 100uF (for 5V Mode) and
1000uF (for 15V/20V Mode) capacitance shall not trigger any protections
or cause the adapter to shut down.

-Follow the test item “ >95% reduction , 0.5 period ” in IEC 61000-4-11 Standard.
-The output voltage shall be more than 14.5V at the below condition :
(a) AC Input = 100Vac/50Hz
(b) Load = 45W constant power (instead of constant current)
Spec. for ASUS PD3.0 65W 62368 ADATPER confidential

-The maximum constant current shall be less than 3.6A for Vo < 15V at 90Vac/264Vac.
-The maximum constant current shall be 3.9A ~ 5A for Vo ≥ 15V at 90Vac/264Vac.
-Meet LPS.
-The adapter shall be DC latch off and no component damaged.
-When fault condition is removed and re-plug in DC plug , the output voltage must return
to the normal condition.
-The adapter cannot have any safety issue or be damaged when the load condition is
before over current protection point (OTP is allowed).

-Maximum output voltage can’t be over 35% for Vo ≥ 15V and 50% for other Vo rating.
-The adapter shall be AC latch off and no component damaged.
-When fault condition is removed and re-plug in AC plug , the output voltage must return
to the normal condition.
Spec. for ASUS PD3.0 65W 62368 ADATPER confidential

-The adapter shall be DC latch off and no component damaged.
-When fault condition is removed and re-plug in DC plug , the output voltage must
return to the normal condition.

-The adapter shall be AC or DC latch off and no component damaged.
-No fire and no melted of the enclosure.
-When fault condition is removed and re-plug in AC or DC plug , the output
voltage must return to the normal condition.
Spec. for ASUS PD3.0 65W 62368 ADATPER confidential

-The power supply shall be designed and produced to have a MTBF of 150,000 operation
hours at 90% confidence – level while operating under the following condition
-AC input voltage: 100 and 240Vrms
-Ambient Temp. : 25°C

-The power supply must be designed to operate for 13,140 power on hours.
-AC input voltage: 100 and 240Vrms
-Ambient Temp. : 25°C

- More than 4 hours at 40°C, normal input voltage.
- AC on/off must be tested.

-Follow ASUS RD Test Plan for NB Adapter Rev04
Spec. for ASUS PD3.0 65W 62368 ADATPER confidential

- The power supply unit shall follow the safety standard ( IEC60950 , IEC62368 )
- Certificate : Follow safety control table
- Trademark : ASUS

- Insulation resistance shall be > 30M ohm at 500Vdc between primary Live, Neutral and
secondary.

-Primary to Secondary : 3.0KVac or 4242Vdc for 1minute
-Primary to F.G :1.5KVac for 1minute
Spec. for ASUS PD3.0 65W 62368 ADATPER confidential

-The power supply leakage current shall be less than 20 uA @240Vac/50Hz
-Test with AC cable 90cm (DT Type)

-Lighting Surge : ±1KV (L-N) ; ± 2KV (L-FG; N-FG)
-Impulse Noise Test: 1KV
-Criteria A

-The power supply shall comply with a following RFI/EMI standards when tested in a
system configuration.
-F.C.C part15
-CISPR22 class B
-The limits shall be meet with a margin more than 6dB with all system applicable.

This Adapter is capable to withstand ESD test voltage at any point around the enclosure
as below.
±15KV air discharge Performance Criterion B
±12KV air discharge Performance Criterion A.
±8KV contact discharge Performance Criterion A.

-Follow ASUS RD Test Plan for NB Adapter Rev05
Spec. for ASUS PD3.0 65W 62368 ADATPER confidential
-Operation: 0~40°C ;Storage: -30~80°C
-Operation: 5~90% ; Storage: 5~95%

- Follow ASUS RD Test Plan for NB Adapter Rev04
